						<summary>

						<p>On the west wall of the Kāśi-Viśvānātha temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">[Vī]rarājēndradēva: Year 20 = 1226—27 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription, of which the beginning of all the lines are lost, records a gift of one <hi rend="italic">achchu</hi> of money by Śōḻan Ilaṅkēśvaradēvaṉ to the temple of Tiruvālandurai-uḍaiyār at Tiruvālandurai in Karaivaḻi-nāḍu, for the decoration <hi rend="italic">(tiru-mēlpūchchu)</hi> of the idol.</p>						

						</summary>
